adminLiquidateAll(bytes,address).details: Only callable by admin. Burns all LP, swaps to stablecoin, transfers to vault

params.aggregator: Address of the swap aggregator to use
params.swapData: Calldata for swapping non-stablecoin token to stablecoin (from Kodiak API)

adminRescueTokens(address,address,uint25.details: Only callable by admin. Use to recover tokens from old/misconfigured hooks

params.token: Address of ERC20 token to rescue

adminSwapAndReturnToVault(address,uint25.details: Use this to rescue stuck HONEY or other tokens after LP burns

params.aggregator: Aggregator address from Kodiak quote API
params.swapData: Swap calldata from Kodiak quote API
params.tokenIn: Address of token to swap (e.g., HONEY)

ensureFundsAvailable(uint256).details: Implementations must ensure at least `amount` stablecoins are available      in the vault by the end of the call (e.g., remove liquidity and send      assets back to the vault).

params.amount: Amount of stablecoin assets the vault needs available (asset decimals)

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleGranted} event.

onAfterDeposit(uint256).details: Implementations may pull `assets` from the vault (requires prior approval)      and deposit them to Kodiak (single-sided via Island Router or double-sided).

params.assets: Amount of stablecoin assets newly deposited into the vault (asset decimals)

onAfterDepositWithSwaps(uint256,address,.details: Vault calls this with swap calldata from Kodiak quote API for assettoken0 and assettoken1.

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been revoked `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `callerConfirmation`. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

adminLiquidateAll(bytes,address).notice: Admin function to liquidate all Island LP and return funds to vault

adminRescueTokens(address,address,uint25.notice: Emergency function to rescue any ERC20 tokens stuck in hook

adminSwapAndReturnToVault(address,uint25.notice: Admin function to swap stuck non-stablecoin tokens and send to vault

ensureFundsAvailable(uint256).notice: Called by the vault before transferring out assets to the user.

getIslandLPBalance().notice: Get Island LP balance held by this hook.

onAfterDeposit(uint256).notice: Called by the vault immediately after assets are deposited into the vault.

onAfterDepositWithSwaps(uint256,address,.notice: Deposit with pre-fetched Kodiak backend swaps (Beefy-style).

transferIslandLP(address,uint256).notice: Transfer Island LP tokens from the hook to a recipient vault (for yield transfers).
